Note: Morphological Operations

Process erode_image with image as Image and kernel_size as Integer:
    Let processor be create_image_processor with backend as GPU_COMPUTE_SHADER
    Let morphology_filter be create_erosion_filter with kernel_size as kernel_size
    
    Return apply_image_filter with processor as processor and image as image and filter as morphology_filter

Process dilate_image with image as Image and kernel_size as Integer:
    Let processor be create_image_processor with backend as GPU_COMPUTE_SHADER
    Let morphology_filter be create_dilation_filter with kernel_size as kernel_size
    
    Return apply_image_filter with processor as processor and image as image and filter as morphology_filter

Process open_image with image as Image and kernel_size as Integer:
    Let eroded be erode_image with image as image and kernel_size as kernel_size
    Return dilate_image with image as eroded and kernel_size as kernel_size

Process close_image with image as Image and kernel_size as Integer:
    Let dilated be dilate_image with image as image and kernel_size as kernel_size
    Return erode_image with image as dilated and kernel_size as kernel_size

Note: Geometric Transformations

Process apply_perspective_transform with image as Image and source_points as List[core.Vector2D] and destination_points as List[core.Vector2D]:
    Let processor be create_image_processor with backend as GPU_COMPUTE_SHADER
    Let transform_matrix be calculate_perspective_matrix with source as source_points and dest as destination_points
    Let perspective_filter be create_perspective_filter with matrix as transform_matrix
    
    Return apply_image_filter with processor as processor and image as image and filter as perspective_filter

Process apply_affine_transform with image as Image and transform_matrix as List[Float]:
    Let processor be create_image_processor with backend as GPU_COMPUTE_SHADER
    Let affine_filter be create_affine_filter with matrix as transform_matrix
    
    Return apply_image_filter with processor as processor and image as image and filter as affine_filter

Process correct_barrel_distortion with image as Image and k1 as Float and k2 as Float:
    Let processor be create_image_processor with backend as GPU_COMPUTE_SHADER
    Let distortion_filter be create_barrel_distortion_correction_filter with k1 as k1 and k2 as k2
    
    Return apply_image_filter with processor as processor and image as image and filter as distortion_filter

Note: Utility Functions

Process get_pixel with image as Image and x as Integer and y as Integer:
    If x is less than 0 or x is greater than or equal to image.width or y is less than 0 or y is greater than or equal to image.height:
        Return core.create_color_rgba with red as 0.0 and green as 0.0 and blue as 0.0 and alpha as 0.0
    
    Let pixel_index be calculate_pixel_index with image as image and x as x and y as y
    Return extract_pixel_color with image as image and index as pixel_index

Process set_pixel with image as Image and x as Integer and y as Integer and color as core.Color:
    If x is less than 0 or x is greater than or equal to image.width or y is less than 0 or y is greater than or equal to image.height:
        Return
    
    Let pixel_index be calculate_pixel_index with image as image and x as x and y as y
    Call write_pixel_color with image as image and index as pixel_index and color as color

Process clone_image with image as Image:
    Let cloned_data be copy_pixel_buffer with data as image.pixel_data
    
    Let cloned_image be image
    Set cloned_image.pixel_data to cloned_data
    Set cloned_image.gpu_texture_handle to 0
    
    Return cloned_image

Process create_thumbnail with image as Image and max_width as Integer and max_height as Integer:
    Let aspect_ratio be image.width divided by image.height
    Let thumb_width be max_width
    Let thumb_height be max_height
    
    If image.width is greater than image.height:
        Set thumb_height to math_module.floor with value as thumb_width divided by aspect_ratio
    Otherwise:
        Set thumb_width to math_module.floor with value as thumb_height multiplied by aspect_ratio
    
    Return resize_image with image as image and new_width as thumb_width and new_height as thumb_height and filter_type as GAUSSIAN_BLUR

Process blend_images with base_image as Image and overlay_image as Image and blend_mode as BlendMode and opacity as Float:
    Let processor be create_image_processor with backend as GPU_COMPUTE_SHADER
    Let blend_filter be create_blend_filter with mode as blend_mode and opacity as opacity and overlay as overlay_image
    
    Return apply_image_filter with processor as processor and image as base_image and filter as blend_filter

Type BlendMode is:
    | NORMAL
    | MULTIPLY
    | SCREEN
    | OVERLAY
    | SOFT_LIGHT
    | HARD_LIGHT
    | COLOR_DODGE
    | COLOR_BURN
    | DARKEN
    | LIGHTEN
    | DIFFERENCE
    | EXCLUSION
    | HUE
    | SATURATION
    | COLOR
    | LUMINOSITY

Note: Implementation Stubs and Helper Functions

Process create_image_processor with backend as ProcessingBackend:
    Let metadata be dict_utils.create_empty_dict
    Call dict_utils.set_value with dict as metadata and key as "type" and value as "image_processor"
    Call dict_utils.set_value with dict as metadata and key as "backend" and value as processing_backend_to_string with backend as backend
    
    Return ImageProcessor with:\
        processing_backend as backend and\
        filter_cache as create_filter_cache and\
        kernel_cache as create_kernel_cache and\
        gpu_context as create_gpu_context and\
        thread_pool as create_thread_pool and\
        memory_pool as create_memory_pool and\
        ai_enhancer as create_ai_image_enhancer and\
        performance_profiler as create_processing_profiler and\
        metadata as metadata

Process calculate_bytes_per_pixel with format as PixelFormat:
    Match format:
        When GRAYSCALE_8:
            Return 1
        When GRAYSCALE_16:
            Return 2
        When GRAYSCALE_32F:
            Return 4
        When RGB_8:
            Return 3
        When RGB_16:
            Return 6
        When RGB_32F:
            Return 12
        When RGBA_8:
            Return 4
        When RGBA_16:
            Return 8
        When RGBA_32F:
            Return 16
        When BGR_8:
            Return 3
        When BGRA_8:
            Return 4
        Otherwise:
            Return 4

Process calculate_bit_depth with format as PixelFormat:
    Match format:
        When GRAYSCALE_8, RGB_8, RGBA_8, BGR_8, BGRA_8:
            Return 8
        When GRAYSCALE_16, RGB_16, RGBA_16:
            Return 16
        When GRAYSCALE_32F, RGB_32F, RGBA_32F:
            Return 32
        Otherwise:
            Return 8

Process pixel_format_to_string with format as PixelFormat:
    Match format:
        When GRAYSCALE_8:
            Return "grayscale_8"
        When RGB_8:
            Return "rgb_8"
        When RGBA_8:
            Return "rgba_8"
        When RGB_32F:
            Return "rgb_32f"
        When RGBA_32F:
            Return "rgba_32f"
        Otherwise:
            Return "unknown"

Process processing_backend_to_string with backend as ProcessingBackend:
    Match backend:
        When CPU_SIMD:
            Return "cpu_simd"
        When GPU_OPENCL:
            Return "gpu_opencl"
        When GPU_CUDA:
            Return "gpu_cuda"
        When GPU_COMPUTE_SHADER:
            Return "gpu_compute_shader"
        When AI_ACCELERATOR:
            Return "ai_accelerator"
        Otherwise:
            Return "unknown"

Process create_pixel_buffer with size as Integer:
    Let buffer be list_utils.create_empty_list
    For i from 0 to size:
        Call list_utils.append with list as buffer and item as 0
    Return buffer

Process create_default_image_metadata:
    Return ImageMetadata with:\
        creation_date as datetime_module.get_current_date_string and\
        camera_make as "" and\
        camera_model as "" and\
        exposure_time as 0.0 and\
        f_number as 0.0 and\
        iso_speed as 0 and\
        focal_length as 0.0 and\
        white_balance as "auto" and\
        orientation as 1 and\
        gps_latitude as 0.0 and\
        gps_longitude as 0.0 and\
        artist as "" and\
        copyright as "" and\
        software as "Runa Graphics Library" and\
        color_profile as create_default_color_profile and\
        custom_metadata as dict_utils.create_empty_dict

Process create_no_compression_info:
    Return CompressionInfo with:\
        compression_type as NONE and\
        quality as 1.0 and\
        lossless as true and\
        progressive as false and\
        compression_ratio as 1.0 and\
        original_size as 0 and\
        compressed_size as 0

Process create_default_image_flags with has_alpha as Boolean:
    Return ImageFlags with:\
        has_alpha as has_alpha and\
        has_transparency as false and\
        is_hdr as false and\
        is_animated as false and\
        is_cubemap as false and\
        is_array as false and\
        is_3d as false and\
        is_compressed as false and\
        is_gpu_resident as false

Process create_default_color_profile:
    Return ColorProfile with:\
        profile_name as "sRGB IEC61966-2.1" and\
        profile_data as list_utils.create_empty_list and\
        white_point as core.create_vector2d with x as 0.3127 and y as 0.3290 and\
        primaries as list_utils.create_empty_list and\
        gamma as 2.2 and\
        rendering_intent as PERCEPTUAL

Process create_error_image with message as String:
    Let error_image be create_image with width as 1 and height as 1 and channels as 3 and pixel_format as RGB_8
    Call dict_utils.set_value with dict as error_image.metadata.custom_metadata and key as "error_message" and value as message
    Return error_image

Note: File Format Handlers (Stubs)

Process extract_file_extension with path as String:
    Let path_length be string_utils.get_string_length with string as path
    Let dot_index be string_utils.find_last_char with string as path and char as "."
    If dot_index is greater than or equal to 0:
        Return string_utils.substring with string as path and start as dot_index plus 1 and length as path_length minus dot_index minus 1
    Return ""

Process detect_image_format_from_extension with extension as String:
    Let lower_ext be string_utils.to_lowercase with string as extension
    Match lower_ext:
        When "jpg", "jpeg":
            Return "JPEG"
        When "png":
            Return "PNG"
        When "webp":
            Return "WEBP"
        When "tiff", "tif":
            Return "TIFF"
        When "bmp":
            Return "BMP"
        When "gif":
            Return "GIF"
        When "exr":
            Return "EXR"
        When "hdr":
            Return "HDR"
        When "raw", "cr2", "nef", "arw":
            Return "RAW"
        Otherwise:
            Return "UNKNOWN"

Process load_jpeg_image with path as String:
    Note: JPEG loading implementation would go here
    Return create_image with width as 1 and height as 1 and channels as 3 and pixel_format as RGB_8

Process load_png_image with path as String:
